From January onwards, households will have to pay a surcharge not only for all types of energy but also for water and sanitation, heating supplies and in some places rents will also increase.
So families will have to draw up to a hundred crowns a month from their wallets from January onwards.
Electricity increases by 4.6 percent, gas by almost 2 percent, in some places you will have to pay up to a tenth more for water supply and in many places central heating supplies will also be more expensive.
The increase in electricity is expected to be close to 100 crowns a year for apartment households, more than it is currently.
However, all suppliers have reduced electricity prices given the sensitive development to encourage the production of renewable energy, particularly photovoltaic batteries.
