The Americans have a new "smart weapon"
The US military has sent a new "smart" weapon to Afghanistan, known only as code XM-25.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will influence the conflict there with the Taliban and "change the game" to their advantage.
The new weapon is like a super-precise cannon.
Its projectiles are guided by laser with a precision of a few meters.
The 25 mm caliber ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly explosive, actually works like small grenades.
The ammunition can be programmed in such a way that it will explode at the point of contact with the target but also at any point in its ballistic trajectory.
So it can be used against an enemy who hides behind an obstacle, a wall, or a ditch.
He's also not protected from above, and when a deadly rain of steel blasts falls on him, it can knock him out of battle too.
According to Richard Audette, who was involved in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon to use "smart" technology.
"The soldier essentially uses it in such a way that he finds the target, sends a laser beam to it that determines the distance, thus obtaining a precise point of aim, according to which he corrects his point of aim and presses on the detachment.
"Let's say you aimed at 543 meters".
"When you press the trigger, the weapon loads and fires at a distance of about 1, 2, 3 meters", Audette said.
