Snow events continue to cause traffic problems, particularly on the secondary network in Brittany, and may disrupt some economic activities.
Twenty-four departments are now on orange alert due to the risk of snow and ice.
The Eure, Eure-et-Loir, Deux-Sèvres and Vienna have joined the 20 departments already on orange alert, 18 since Wednesday afternoon and two, the Dordogne and Gironde, later in the night.
